D-Branes on parallelizable plane-waves 


In this section we study the existence of BPS -branes in s
backgrounds. -branes have been studied in various plane-wave 
backgrounds (e.g. see). In 
general 
there are two ways of addressing the question of -branes, one is 
through open strings with Dirichlet boundary conditions, as it was first 
introduced in, or through closed strings and the boundary 
state formulation
.  Here we follow the construction via open strings.  As we 
will show, due to presence of the -field, three different situations can arise.








To start with, let us focus on the bosonic modes. First we note that, as
is evident from eq. (),  
the light-cone gauge condition fixes the boundary condition the or   
component to be Neumann. Therefore,  lies inside the worldvolume of all 
-branes we are going to study. As for the other components, we 
start with the light-cone action (). This leads to the  
eq. () and the boundary conditions
